sia Sponsor.</b> <br>          Your sponsor will be your lifeguard, spiritual advisor, and friend throughout your recovery process.  It's a long journey and you can always use a guide.            <p><b>2. Stay Cool!</b> <br>            More than anything, you've got to be as cool as a penguin pushing ice cubes.  Relax!  3rd Dimensia isn't the end of the world. Just get with the program and go with the flow.  You'll be glad you did!</p>            <p><b>3.  Leave the Bad Attitude at Home!</b><br>        Sometimes we get patients who think they know how to take care of themselves.  If that were the case, they'd be working for us!  Seriously, our trained staff knows how to expertly treat ADAD, and it makes their jobs a lot easier when patients cooperate.  </p>		<p><b>4. It's not a Crime.</b><br>        You haven't done anything wrong.  3rd Dimensia is completely normal.  If you think you're alone, you're not.  Normal people all over the world suffer from the disorder.  In fact, many important celebrities like Tevon Lightman, Dr Karen Lootus, and celebrity chef Peter Pepper have recently brought their very private battles with 3rd Dimensia into the public eye. </p>		<p><b>5.  Open your Mind.</b><br>        There's a whole third of the world out that there that you're missing out on.  Additional Dimension Adjustment Therapy consists of complex treatments and special medications, but you've also got to want to see the world for what it is - Three Dimensions of Freedom!</p></td>      </tr>      <tr>        <td colspan="4">&nbsp;</td>      </tr>    </table>    </td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td><img src="images/bottom_line.gif" width="799" height="26"></td>  </tr></table></body></html>